{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"27f93a07-ecf5-4aa9-b28a-73c3cbfc7711","content":"Use **`dotnet test`**, not `dotnet run`.\n\nSince your project has `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`, `dotnet test` will use the Microsoft Testing Platform under the hood, which is what enables the hot reload extension. Just run:\n\n```bash\ndotnet test\n```\n\nThe `Microsoft.Testing.Extensions.HotReload` package hooks into the Testing Platform's execution pipeline. When the `TESTINGPLATFORM_HOTRELOAD_ENABLED` environment variable is set, it watches for file changes and re-runs affected tests automatically — but this only activates through the test host, not a generic `dotnet run`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"aa68978b-a410-4741-8fc8-03687f76eb44","outputTokens":161,"requestId":"BC53:26D998:1DF259B:213DCA8:69FA988B"},"id":"8c354a93-eb11-4669-9846-e9e4fb7b5030","timestamp":"2026-05-06T01:25:37.319Z","parentId":"a21bbd9c-894e-4f6b-9a55-992494cf31e3"}
